This was in reference to EACC’s declaration that former Kiambu governor Ferdinand Waititu was unfit to run in next month’s Nairobi gubernatorial by-election, which was occasioned by the impeachment of Mike Sonko.
Mr Havi’s declaration brings to question the place of the Constitution, state agencies and arms of government as far as issues of integrity are concerned. The LSK chief cited a case where IEBC failed to clear Wavinya Ndeti in the run-up to the 2013 elections, which was overturned by the High Court. This, for him, implied that only the court had the final word.



